.This twentieth anniversary edition of Written in Stone includes a new preface and an extensive afterword that takes account of recent events in cities, schools and universities, and public spaces throughout the United States and elsewhere. Twenty years on, Levinson's work is more timely and relevant than ever.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aFlagsxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aMonumentsxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aMulticulturalismzUnited States. 0aPolitical culturezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical culturezUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999z978311071360240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478004349zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478004349423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478004349.jpg  a978-3-11-071360-2  DUK Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999c1964d1999  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles